{"page_content": "C A S E  S T U D Y  2\nCoding co-pilot \u2013 evaluation\nAgent characteristics\n1. Function\n3. Predictability\n4. Autonomy\n5. Authority\nAssists human developers with code generation and debugging\nDeterministic\nNon-deterministic\n2. Role\nSpecialist\nGeneralist\nLow\nHigh\nLow\nHigh\nOperational context\n6. Use case\n7. Environment\nSimple\nComplex\nCoding co-pilot\nA coding co-pilot operates in the software development \ndomain, assisting programmers within their coding \nenvironment by generating, completing and debugging \ncode to improve productivity and reduce errors.\nCoding co-pilot \u2013 evaluation\nEvaluation starts with controlled tests in development \nenvironments to verify productivity gains while ensuring \nsafety, reliability and compliance. Evaluation follows several \nkey steps including:\n\t\u2013\nContextualization: Testing across coding tasks such as \ncode generation, debugging and documentation to reflect \nreal workflows\n\t\u2013\nPerformance: Measuring task success rate, completion \ntime and error frequency, along with system metrics like \ntool-call success\n\t\u2013\nRobustness: Exposing the agent to ambiguous or \nconflicting code to assess recovery, error handling  \nand adaptability\n\t\u2013\nHuman trust: Gathering user feedback on reliability  \nand usefulness\n\t\u2013\nMonitoring: Using continuous logging to detect performance \ndrift, anomalous tool use or regressions after deployment\nAI Agents in Action: Foundations for Evaluation and Governance\n20", "metadata": {"producer": "Adobe PDF Library 18.0", "creator": "Adobe InDesign 21.0 (Macintosh)", "creationdate": "2025-12-05T09:39:21+00:00", "source": "D:\\Users\\wpoga\\Documents\\Ebooks\\Artificial Intelligence\\WEF_AI_Agents_in_Action_Foundations_for_Evaluation_and_Governance_2025.pdf", "file_path": "D:\\Users\\wpoga\\Documents\\Ebooks\\Artificial Intelligence\\WEF_AI_Agents_in_Action_Foundations_for_Evaluation_and_Governance_2025.pdf", "total_pages": 34, "format": "PDF 1.7", "title": "", "author": "", "subject": "", "keywords": "", "moddate": "2025-12-05T11:15:47+01:00", "trapped": "", "modDate": "D:20251205111547+01'00'", "creationDate": "D:20251205093921Z", "page": 19}, "type": "Document"}
